<DOC><DOCNO> AP900930-0014 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NY-09-30-90 0053EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-ChemicalFire     09-30 0135</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Chemical Fire,0127</SECOND><HEAD>Chemical Plant Burns Near Houston</HEAD><NOTE>Eds: Tubilor cq in 2nd graf</NOTE><DATELINE>MAGNOLIA, Texas (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A fire raced through a chemical plantSaturday, injuring two firefighters and forcing the evacuation oflocal residents.   The four-alarm blaze at the Tubilor Protectors of America plantwas still burning late Saturday, firefighters said.   Montgomery County sheriff's officers ordered a one-mile areaaround the plant to be evacuated, and extended the order to twomiles on the northwest side, which was downwind.   ``The whole building is burning,'' said sheriff's spokeswomanDebbie Yancy.   The cause of the fire was not immediately determined.   The plant, which processed several chemicals including theflammable gas methyl chloride, is about 25 miles northwest ofHouston.</TEXT></DOC>